MALARIA - INDIA (11): (CHHATTISGARH)
*****************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Tue 7 Dec 2010
Source: Bombay News.Net, Indo Asian News Service (IANS) report [edited]
<http://www.bombaynews.net/story/716583>


Health Minister Amar Agrawal informed the state assembly on Tuesday
[7 Dec 2010] that 24 people have died of malaria and over one lakh
(100 000) people have tested positive for the disease in Chhattisgarh
this year [2010]

Until 15 Nov 2010 122 939 people were found positive for malaria, the
minister informed the house in a written reply to a question by
Congress member and Leader of Opposition Ravindra Choubey.

Between 2004-2009, 26 people died due to malaria, he said.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to the latest World Malaria Report, from 2009
(<http://www.who.int/malaria/world_malaria_report_2009/en/>), malaria
is highly endemic in most of Chhattisgarh with an annual incidence
between 1 and 100 cases per 1000 population.

Chhattisgarh can be located on the maps of India at
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chhattisgarh> and
<http://healthmap.org/r/0iw4>. - Mod.EP]
